WEBVTT

00:02:01.387 --> 00:02:02.856
Frozen, frozen, hard.

00:02:04.290 --> 00:02:05.859
No good after all.

00:02:07.260 --> 00:02:08.862
It's full of dioxins.

00:02:09.129 --> 00:02:11.898
I had saved this as
evidence a while back.

00:02:16.302 --> 00:02:18.571
Don't eat it,
you malnutritioned kid!

00:02:20.707 --> 00:02:23.476
Then you want to catch a fraud?
A matrimonial fraud?

00:02:23.543 --> 00:02:24.711
Guess I have no choice.

00:02:24.777 --> 00:02:26.913
What kind of fraud? Is it big?

00:02:27.180 --> 00:02:28.681
Smallest of the small fry.

00:02:28.748 --> 00:02:30.783
I don't think Spike
will be up for this.

00:02:31.718 --> 00:02:33.920
Ed wants chicken kabobs!

00:02:36.156 --> 00:02:37.624
Guess I'll do it alone.

00:02:40.527 --> 00:02:42.395
You have got to be kidding!

00:02:50.703 --> 00:02:52.805
Give me a break.

00:02:59.846 --> 00:03:01.447
{\an8}This stinks!

00:03:04.884 --> 00:03:06.252
Really.

00:03:06.319 --> 00:03:09.622
Weren't you taught
that you should wipe your own butt?

00:03:12.825 --> 00:03:16.195
I've been thinking of who
you remind me of.

00:03:16.796 --> 00:03:19.566
I know now.
That guy with the thin eyebrows.

00:03:19.632 --> 00:03:22.335
Whitney Hagas Matsumoto.

00:03:23.570 --> 00:03:26.606
I wonder why I suddenly
was reminded of him.

00:03:26.973 --> 00:03:29.943
Do you want to know something
about my past nobody else knows?

00:03:52.799 --> 00:03:56.336
Miss Manley, does she look
resuscitated to you?

00:03:56.402 --> 00:03:58.504
Yes, she does, doctor.

00:03:58.571 --> 00:04:01.741
Miss Manley, does she look
like an old woman to you?

00:04:01.941 --> 00:04:03.710
No, she doesn't, doctor.

00:04:03.776 --> 00:04:06.713
Do you think she has been
successfully defrosted?

00:04:06.779 --> 00:04:08.481
I believe so, doctor.

00:04:08.548 --> 00:04:11.284
Can you hear me?

00:04:12.785 --> 00:04:14.787
I am Dr. Baccus.

00:04:14.854 --> 00:04:19.592
Baccus, as in the Baccus that
drowned more humans than Neptune.

00:04:19.659 --> 00:04:20.760
Do you know about him?

00:04:21.828 --> 00:04:26.733
But I used to be an alcoholic.
Baccus was drowning thanks to Baccus.

00:04:26.799 --> 00:04:28.935
Hey, that was great!

00:04:34.007 --> 00:04:35.541
All right, open wide.

00:04:38.611 --> 00:04:42.949
No problems. You have no wounds left,
and the cells are dividing nicely.

00:04:43.016 --> 00:04:46.052
Now you only have
one problem to solve.

00:04:46.653 --> 00:04:48.788
Oh, it's just a simple process.

00:04:48.855 --> 00:04:52.592
The 30 million for the basic operation,
and 54 years' worth of interest.

00:04:52.659 --> 00:04:54.060
Hey, how much is that?

00:04:54.627 --> 00:05:01.434
273 million. Add to that the hospital
fees for a total of 300,028,000 woolongs.

00:05:01.501 --> 00:05:05.438
Yes, if you pay up that much,
you will be free. Do you understand?

00:05:05.505 --> 00:05:06.472
I don't understand.

00:05:06.539 --> 00:05:07.707
Yes, that's it.

00:05:07.940 --> 00:05:09.008
What?!

00:05:09.075 --> 00:05:11.511
Where is this?

00:05:11.577 --> 00:05:13.579
Who am I?

00:05:18.518 --> 00:05:19.585
Miss Manley?

00:05:20.520 --> 00:05:22.755
She is not acting, doctor.

00:05:27.493 --> 00:05:30.096
I am Whitney Hagas Matsumoto,
your lawyer.

00:05:31.030 --> 00:05:32.632
Lawyer?

00:05:33.032 --> 00:05:38.838
At the request of the Totus Insurance
Company, I did some research on your past.

00:05:38.905 --> 00:05:40.840
Miss Faye Valentine.

00:05:40.907 --> 00:05:43.076
Is that really my name?

00:05:43.710 --> 00:05:45.344
It's a lovely name.

00:05:45.878 --> 00:05:47.046
It suits you very well.

00:05:47.980 --> 00:05:49.082
And?

00:05:49.348 --> 00:05:51.851
How much of your memory
do you still have?

00:05:52.485 --> 00:05:53.586
This is a TV,

00:05:53.653 --> 00:05:56.856
this is a hot water pot,
and this is a cellular phone.

00:05:56.923 --> 00:05:59.125
I know everything...

00:05:59.392 --> 00:06:00.960
except about myself.

00:06:01.027 --> 00:06:02.061
I see.

00:06:02.128 --> 00:06:03.129
And?

00:06:03.396 --> 00:06:06.099
According to the materials
that remain, when you were 20...

00:06:06.699 --> 00:06:08.367
Well, you are still 20.

00:06:08.434 --> 00:06:10.770
You seem to have been
involved in a serious accident.

00:06:10.837 --> 00:06:11.971
Accident?

00:06:12.038 --> 00:06:15.575
Such that medical technology back
then could not completely cure you.

00:06:15.641 --> 00:06:17.710
I'm totally fine, as you can see.

00:06:17.777 --> 00:06:19.412
Not a scratch on my body.

00:06:19.479 --> 00:06:20.980
Wait, what do you mean,
"back then"?

00:06:21.547 --> 00:06:23.750
That was 54 years ago.

00:06:25.118 --> 00:06:30.656
You have been in cold-sleep, or rather
cryogenically preserved, to this day.

00:06:30.723 --> 00:06:35.695
And you were able to reawaken now that
you could get the treatment you needed.

00:06:37.630 --> 00:06:39.699
Just like Sleeping Beauty.

00:06:40.166 --> 00:06:42.902
-You're kidding, right?
-I am being serious.

00:06:43.536 --> 00:06:45.171
Then this is a dream.

00:06:48.040 --> 00:06:50.610
No, it is definitely 2068 now.

00:06:50.676 --> 00:06:52.979
And this isn't a TV...

00:06:53.713 --> 00:06:55.515
but a washing machine.

00:06:55.581 --> 00:06:58.618
And this isn't a hot water pot,
but a face-washing machine.

00:06:58.684 --> 00:07:01.754
And this is not a telephone,
but a thermometer.

00:07:02.121 --> 00:07:03.990
You put this round segment
in your mouth.

00:07:04.056 --> 00:07:05.024
Don't mock me!

00:07:05.091 --> 00:07:07.994
You just start saying stuff like that,
and you expect me to--

00:07:09.061 --> 00:07:13.699
<i>Body temperature: 34.5 degrees Celsius.</i>
<i>Pulse: 54. Blood pressure: 40/75.</i>

00:07:13.900 --> 00:07:15.668
-Still low.
-Wait a minute!

00:07:15.735 --> 00:07:19.806
Your memories end back when cellular
telephones still looked like this.

00:07:19.872 --> 00:07:21.140
Then tell me!

00:07:21.207 --> 00:07:23.176
What kind of accident?
What was I like?

00:07:23.443 --> 00:07:24.744
Who am I?

00:07:24.811 --> 00:07:27.213
Calm down. If you get excited, you...

00:07:27.480 --> 00:07:29.115
What? What is going to happen.

00:07:35.021 --> 00:07:36.756
You'll get sleepy.

00:08:21.234 --> 00:08:22.568
<i>Would you like one?</i>

00:08:36.616 --> 00:08:37.717
Hey!

00:08:37.783 --> 00:08:38.851
Hey!

00:08:38.918 --> 00:08:40.920
Hey!

00:08:46.692 --> 00:08:47.793
Wait!

00:09:06.712 --> 00:09:07.613
Miss Valentine!

00:09:15.988 --> 00:09:17.123
Wait!

00:09:17.990 --> 00:09:18.891
Don't come near me!

00:09:18.958 --> 00:09:20.560
What can you do by running away?

00:09:28.100 --> 00:09:29.936
Miss Valentine.

00:09:31.637 --> 00:09:34.040
I can't pay 300 million.

00:09:36.042 --> 00:09:39.879
It's unreasonable for them to resuscitate
me and then expect me to pay the debt.

00:09:40.613 --> 00:09:42.715
I don't even know
anything about myself.

00:09:43.883 --> 00:09:45.751
What should I do?

00:09:51.791 --> 00:09:54.727
We can take it slow about the debt.

00:09:55.294 --> 00:09:57.129
I will help you.

00:09:58.030 --> 00:10:00.700
Your memory might come
back to you someday.

00:10:03.035 --> 00:10:06.072
If you keep living,
you might meet someone wonderful.

00:10:18.884 --> 00:10:20.252
What... is this?

00:10:20.886 --> 00:10:22.121
An ID.

00:10:22.321 --> 00:10:24.657
This way, if you die,
or if you forget yourself,

00:10:24.724 --> 00:10:26.959
they will know who you are
and where you're from.

00:10:29.128 --> 00:10:32.098
And I don't have that.

00:11:32.758 --> 00:11:34.193
-What?!
-The collection agency!

00:11:34.260 --> 00:11:37.163
-The insurance company got impatient!
-What are we going to do?

00:11:51.177 --> 00:11:53.012
At this rate, we're both doomed.

00:11:53.079 --> 00:11:55.247
-Get out of the car and run.
-What about you?

00:11:55.414 --> 00:11:57.817
We'll meet up at the doctor's place.
All right?

00:11:58.451 --> 00:12:00.052
Why are you helping me?

00:12:01.487 --> 00:12:04.857
The prince must protect
his sleeping beauty.

00:12:22.208 --> 00:12:24.276
We just went through the paperwork.

00:12:24.343 --> 00:12:29.315
He told us to hand you all of his
assets if something happened to him.

00:12:29.815 --> 00:12:34.286
If you give us a thumbprint here,
everything he owns will be yours.

00:12:34.920 --> 00:12:36.021
Whitney.

00:12:36.822 --> 00:12:38.791
You really cared for me.

00:12:39.892 --> 00:12:41.760
Now, put your thumb here.

00:12:49.835 --> 00:12:52.071
Why are the numbers all red?

00:12:52.138 --> 00:12:54.907
Well, they say that debt is an asset.

00:12:54.974 --> 00:12:56.175
Debt?

00:12:59.945 --> 00:13:02.548
You have got to be kidding!

00:13:04.083 --> 00:13:06.385
I was stupid back then,
now that I think about it.

00:13:06.785 --> 00:13:10.256
I mean, he risked
his life to save me.

00:13:10.923 --> 00:13:14.827
His debt was nothing compared to mine.

00:13:15.427 --> 00:13:17.496
It really wasn't that much.

00:13:24.537 --> 00:13:26.472
You were there the whole time?

00:13:27.473 --> 00:13:29.074
Your story was way too long.

00:13:40.252 --> 00:13:41.487
You are a horrible woman.

00:13:42.488 --> 00:13:44.557
I'm sure that guy is
weeping in the afterlife

00:13:44.823 --> 00:13:46.892
now that you ran away
without paying the debt.

00:13:46.959 --> 00:13:49.995
I can't help it.
It's not a sum that I can pay off.

00:13:50.262 --> 00:13:51.931
Now you're being defiant about it.

00:13:51.997 --> 00:13:55.234
I've got some nerve, all right.
I'm much older than you are.

00:13:55.834 --> 00:13:59.371
Your past is all lies.
What was that about Romani?

00:13:59.438 --> 00:14:01.440
Did you make this story up, too?

00:14:02.074 --> 00:14:04.043
It's neither a lie, nor a fake.

00:14:04.343 --> 00:14:05.945
I just don't know the truth.

00:14:06.445 --> 00:14:07.980
Like I can help it.

00:14:08.380 --> 00:14:10.316
Welcome back!

00:14:14.620 --> 00:14:16.989
This guy is known as
the "Madam Killer."

00:14:17.256 --> 00:14:19.191
Well, he's just a cheap
matrimonial fraud.

00:14:19.258 --> 00:14:20.893
Sure doesn't look like one.

00:14:20.960 --> 00:14:24.363
Well, I can do a good job
even by myself.

00:14:24.430 --> 00:14:25.564
Got that?

00:14:36.175 --> 00:14:38.878
Whitney Hagas Matsumoto.

00:14:40.045 --> 00:14:42.948
Hey, long time no see.

00:14:43.582 --> 00:14:47.152
What kind of relationship do they have
that she wants to talk to him alone?

00:14:47.219 --> 00:14:49.188
Apparently it's a pretty
deep relationship.

00:14:49.255 --> 00:14:50.923
An old guy of hers?

00:14:50.990 --> 00:14:52.491
They were made for each other.

00:14:52.925 --> 00:14:55.394
You seem very, very well,
Mr. Lawyer.

00:14:55.995 --> 00:14:58.330
Is it because I'm fat?
Isn't that a biased opinion?

00:14:58.397 --> 00:15:00.099
I demand an explanation.

00:15:01.400 --> 00:15:03.269
I got a fat implant
after that accident.

00:15:03.369 --> 00:15:06.338
Got a little incision around
the armpit, and had it squeezed in.

00:15:06.405 --> 00:15:07.406
Not that!

00:15:09.541 --> 00:15:10.943
It's been three years.

00:15:11.010 --> 00:15:13.412
-You look healthy, I'm glad.
-Yeah, I'm sure you are.

00:15:13.479 --> 00:15:15.948
Do you think you reinvented yourself
by doing that?

00:15:17.316 --> 00:15:18.617
I wanted to start over.

00:15:19.251 --> 00:15:20.252
Start everything over.

00:15:20.319 --> 00:15:22.521
And so you went with matrimonial fraud.

00:15:22.588 --> 00:15:25.658
To think you're a bounty hunter...
This must have been destined.

00:15:25.925 --> 00:15:27.559
So, everyone was in on it?

00:15:29.161 --> 00:15:33.532
Back then, I couldn't do anything else.
Because he sheltered me, the doctor.

00:15:34.700 --> 00:15:36.936
Maybe it was better
to have been caught.

00:15:37.002 --> 00:15:40.306
I couldn't wish for anything more than
you handing me over to the police.

00:15:43.309 --> 00:15:45.110
Is it okay to leave them alone?

00:15:45.177 --> 00:15:46.979
You worried about her?

00:15:47.046 --> 00:15:49.515
I just thought that she might let him go.

00:15:49.581 --> 00:15:51.650
Does she have that much
sympathy in her heart?

00:15:51.717 --> 00:15:54.286
Women as insistent as her
tend to be the ones

00:15:54.353 --> 00:15:57.456
who get emotionally
swayed by their exes.

00:15:57.523 --> 00:15:59.024
Is that so?

00:15:59.091 --> 00:16:01.527
Women don't work on reason.

00:16:02.494 --> 00:16:04.630
Welcome, visitors!

00:16:06.298 --> 00:16:08.634
<i>So, are you the ones</i>
<i>that reported to us?</i>

00:16:08.701 --> 00:16:11.203
<i>Yeah, I want to claim a bounty.</i>

00:16:11.270 --> 00:16:12.204
<i>I see.</i>

00:16:12.271 --> 00:16:14.239
Miss Manley, prepare to rendezvous.

00:16:14.306 --> 00:16:15.207
Yes, inspector.

00:16:17.710 --> 00:16:20.112
I'm glad I was able to
meet you one last time.

00:16:22.081 --> 00:16:23.148
Take care.

00:16:28.554 --> 00:16:31.023
-I won't hand you over to them!
-It's all right.

00:16:31.323 --> 00:16:33.359
You really don't have to mind me!

00:16:39.064 --> 00:16:40.499
Are they ready to depart already?

00:16:40.566 --> 00:16:42.301
Is she gonna let him go?

00:16:42.368 --> 00:16:43.602
She might be letting him go.

00:16:43.669 --> 00:16:45.671
-You wanna bet?
-We're splitting it 60-40.

00:16:46.739 --> 00:16:48.741
Damn it, hurry up, Spike!

00:16:49.008 --> 00:16:50.309
I'm trying!

00:16:52.077 --> 00:16:54.780
It's impossible
to get both of us in this!

00:16:55.047 --> 00:16:58.017
I don't care.
Breathe out some more! Exhale.

00:16:58.550 --> 00:16:59.718
Hey, wait!

00:17:00.452 --> 00:17:02.254
I'm not letting you have him!

00:17:03.756 --> 00:17:07.126
-She took the guy and not the money!
-Jet captured him!

00:17:07.192 --> 00:17:09.628
I have to repay my debt to him.

00:17:09.695 --> 00:17:12.631
So, I have the right to do what I want
with him and the bounty!

00:17:12.698 --> 00:17:15.367
Amazing. She clearly
states a pointless argument.

00:17:15.434 --> 00:17:17.736
That's what I told you.
Women don't work on reason.

00:17:17.803 --> 00:17:19.538
Get me off of this thing!

00:17:19.605 --> 00:17:21.106
Are you gonna let him go?

00:17:21.173 --> 00:17:22.207
We'll see!

00:17:35.087 --> 00:17:37.756
Visitor, thanks for coming!

00:17:42.061 --> 00:17:43.228
Where are you going?

00:17:45.097 --> 00:17:46.565
What are you going to do with me?

00:17:48.100 --> 00:17:49.501
I want you to tell me the truth.

00:17:50.302 --> 00:17:52.404
Why was I there?

00:17:52.471 --> 00:17:55.274
Where does the truth end,
and where do the lies start?

00:17:59.445 --> 00:18:00.479
What are you doing?

00:18:03.182 --> 00:18:04.850
If you're not careful, I'll hit the pod.

00:18:07.219 --> 00:18:08.754
I'm not going to be easy on you!

00:18:11.757 --> 00:18:12.791
That's my line!

00:18:51.530 --> 00:18:53.365
You're causing me a lot of trouble.

00:19:01.206 --> 00:19:02.641
Who am I?

00:19:06.645 --> 00:19:09.248
Do you really want to
know your own past?

00:19:12.284 --> 00:19:14.386
Are you prepared for the consequences?

00:19:15.821 --> 00:19:16.688
I am.

00:19:17.256 --> 00:19:18.157
I see.

00:19:21.293 --> 00:19:22.327
Wait a minute.

00:19:22.394 --> 00:19:23.829
Well, I don't really know myself.

00:19:23.896 --> 00:19:25.297
You're so...

00:19:25.364 --> 00:19:28.534
<i>Who you really are, where you are</i>
<i>from, and where you will go.</i>

00:19:28.600 --> 00:19:32.171
<i>That is a question that every human</i>
<i>asks himself at least once in his life.</i>

00:19:32.237 --> 00:19:32.905
And who are you?

00:19:33.172 --> 00:19:36.542
<i>However, puberty is the only time you</i>
<i>need to worry about things like that.</i>

00:19:36.608 --> 00:19:39.912
<i>Only bored individuals think such</i>
<i>thoughts after a certain age.</i>

00:19:40.445 --> 00:19:42.281
I've heard that voice before.

00:19:43.415 --> 00:19:45.384
<i>Can you see me?</i>

00:19:45.851 --> 00:19:48.587
Is that the doctor and the nurse?

00:19:48.654 --> 00:19:50.189
Seems that way.

00:19:50.255 --> 00:19:52.424
Didn't you say something
the doctor passed away?

00:19:52.491 --> 00:19:53.892
No. I didn't mean it that way.

00:19:53.959 --> 00:19:56.929
You! How many lies do you have
to tell before you're satisfied?

00:19:58.630 --> 00:20:01.700
<i>You were cryogenically</i>
<i>preserved there.</i>

00:20:01.767 --> 00:20:04.570
<i>That we are certain of.</i>
<i>I guarantee it.</i>

00:20:05.904 --> 00:20:07.539
What about my past?

00:20:07.606 --> 00:20:08.774
Who in the world am I?

00:20:08.840 --> 00:20:11.376
<i>I gave you the name Valentine.</i>

00:20:11.843 --> 00:20:13.912
I named you after my favorite song.

00:20:13.979 --> 00:20:18.450
As for everything else, all data was
lost back in that Gate accident.

00:20:18.517 --> 00:20:22.621
<i>So, I don't know who you are,</i>
<i>or why you were put in cold-sleep.</i>

00:20:23.355 --> 00:20:24.723
He wasn't a cop?

00:20:25.624 --> 00:20:28.460
<i>The patrol ship over there.</i>
<i>State your department.</i>

00:20:28.794 --> 00:20:31.597
<i>I repeat. The patrol ship over there.</i>

00:20:31.663 --> 00:20:34.266
<i>State your department</i>
<i>and registration number.</i>

00:20:34.499 --> 00:20:37.469
Doctor, at this rate,
we will be apprehended.

00:20:37.536 --> 00:20:41.540
It's truly unfortunate, but it's best
that we not meddle in this any longer.

00:20:41.607 --> 00:20:42.474
Let's give up.

00:20:42.541 --> 00:20:45.577
<i>So, farewell, Whitney,</i>
<i>take care of yourself.</i>

00:20:45.644 --> 00:20:46.845
<i>We're sorry.</i>

00:20:48.513 --> 00:20:50.782
Hey, wait! Uncle! Uncle!

00:20:51.383 --> 00:20:52.484
Uncle?

00:21:07.466 --> 00:21:09.301
I'll take my bounty here and now!

00:21:10.469 --> 00:21:11.470
There you go!

00:21:14.706 --> 00:21:15.907
Good riddance.

00:21:16.341 --> 00:21:18.910
I guess you're being paid back
for all the lies you told.

00:21:21.446 --> 00:21:22.881
There is one truth I have spoken.

00:21:25.050 --> 00:21:27.653
That I fell in love with
you while you were asleep.

00:21:28.320 --> 00:21:29.688
In love with a sleeping beauty.

00:21:33.292 --> 00:21:34.493
No, just kidding!

00:21:34.826 --> 00:21:36.028
I'm lying! It's a lie!

00:21:42.868 --> 00:21:45.470
Did you want me to come back that badly?

00:21:45.537 --> 00:21:46.838
You sure got a big mouth.

00:21:46.905 --> 00:21:48.540
You were jealous.

00:21:48.607 --> 00:21:51.410
You really are a heartless woman.

00:21:52.944 --> 00:21:56.615
I guess I don't know anything
about my past anymore.

00:21:56.682 --> 00:21:58.617
Isn't that something
that doesn't matter?

00:21:58.684 --> 00:22:01.086
You think that way
because you have a past.

00:22:01.353 --> 00:22:03.622
No matter the past,
you still have a future.

00:22:04.656 --> 00:22:05.590
What's this?

00:22:05.991 --> 00:22:10.362
Your share of the 19,800 on his head.

00:22:10.495 --> 00:22:11.763
19,800?

00:22:12.497 --> 00:22:14.700
The smallest of the small fry.

00:22:15.634 --> 00:22:18.403
It wasn't 198,000?

00:22:19.838 --> 00:22:22.908
I put an extra digit in there.

00:24:10.682 --> 00:24:13.185
<i>So, the next episode</i>
<i>of </i>Cowboy Bebop,

00:24:13.451 --> 00:24:16.521
<i>I admit, is really</i>
<i>heavy and depressing.</i>

00:24:16.588 --> 00:24:20.192
<i>The only people that show up</i>
<i>are well-aged, musty men.</i>

00:24:20.759 --> 00:24:22.828
<i>I hate to say this,</i>
<i>but it is lackluster.</i>

00:24:22.894 --> 00:24:24.529
<i>Children shouldn't watch it.</i>

00:24:24.596 --> 00:24:26.464
<i>Ladies should avoid it, too.</i>

00:24:26.531 --> 00:24:30.235
<i>And to top it off, it's better</i>
<i>for young guys to not watch either.</i>

00:24:30.502 --> 00:24:33.071
<i>Next episode: "Black Dog Serenade."</i>

00:24:33.138 --> 00:24:36.174
<i>Just to all the old guys,</i>
<i>make sure you watch it.</i>

